---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Granny Flats Frankston South | Larger Blocks, Family Solutions | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Granny flat builders for Frankston South — larger 700-1200m² blocks, families, ageing parents and adult children. 1-bed, 2-bed and dual-occupancy. Free design consultation."
  canonical="https://frankstongrannyflats.com.au/frankston-south/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Frankston South &middot; Olivers Hill &middot; Daveys Bay</span>
      <h1>Granny flats in <span class="accent">Frankston South</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Frankston South has the larger blocks of the City of Frankston &mdash; typically
        700&ndash;1,200m&sup2; &mdash; which makes it the suburb where granny flats and
        dual-occupancy second dwellings actually make sense. Most of our Frankston South
        work is for families housing ageing parents or adult children who can&rsquo;t
        afford to buy.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free consultation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Frankston South</span>
      <h2>The Frankston South granny flat story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>The block-size advantage.</h3>
        <p>
          Frankston South was subdivided in the 1960s and 1970s on quarter-acre and
          third-acre lots. Streets off Cranbourne Road, around Overport Park, along
          Robinsons Road and Towerhill Road typically sit on 800&ndash;1,200m&sup2;
          blocks. That makes Frankston City&rsquo;s &ldquo;one second dwelling per
          lot &ge;300m&sup2;&rdquo; rule a non-issue here, and leaves room for proper
          setbacks, separate driveway, separate outdoor area, and even mature trees
          to keep.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Two demographic drivers.</h3>
        <p>
          About <strong>60% of our Frankston South granny flats</strong> are for ageing
          parents moving from a larger family home that&rsquo;s become too much. The
          other 40% are for adult children priced out of buying who want independence
          without the rent. Both groups want similar things: full kitchen and laundry,
          step-free entry, a private outdoor courtyard, separate driveway access.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Olivers Hill / Daveys Bay coastal proximity.</h3>
        <p>
          The southern end of Frankston South (Olivers Hill, Daveys Bay, Sweetwater Creek
          parkland edge) is within 2&ndash;3km of Port Phillip Bay &mdash; close enough
          for AS 4312 salt-zone specification on external metal, stainless fittings,
          and elevated subfloor ventilation. Adds 4&ndash;6% to build cost. Inland of
          Frankston Park (north of McComb Pkwy) is typically outside the moderate-zone
          line and doesn&rsquo;t need the upgrade.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Frankston South jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1-bedroom granny flat 45m&sup2; for ageing parent, $130K&ndash;$170K, VicSmart fast-track</li>
          <li>2-bedroom dual-occupancy 90m&sup2; for adult child + partner, $190K&ndash;$240K, full planning permit</li>
          <li>Subdivision-ready dual-occupancy on 1,000m&sup2;+ blocks, $220K&ndash;$280K, with separate-title pathway in 5 years</li>
          <li>NDIS SDA-compliant 1-bedroom for adult child with disability, $350K&ndash;$500K, with SDA provider rental income</li>
          <li>Detached studio in rear yard near established gum trees (TPZ-aware excavation)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mt-eliza/">Mt Eliza</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mornington/">Mornington</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/carrum-downs/">Carrum Downs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/seaford/">Seaford</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mornington-peninsula/">Mornington Peninsula</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Frankston South design consultation.</h2>
        <p>On-site, 60 minutes. We measure, check the zone, give you the honest answer on what fits the block.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
